<section class="page-head section section--tight">
  <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="figure-note">Last updated {% year %}</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">
        The short version: this site doesn't track you. There are no ads, no analytics, no
        cookies, and no accounts. It's a set of static pages and nothing you do here is sent
        to us or stored.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing. This site has no analytics, no tracking pixels, no cookies, and no contact
        forms. We don't ask for or store any personal information.
      </p>

      <h2>2. The self-check</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/diagnosis.html">self-check</a> runs entirely in your browser. Your answers
        and result never leave your device and are not saved &mdash; refreshing the page clears them.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        The site is hosted on GitHub Pages. Like any web host, GitHub may automatically process
        basic technical information (such as your IP address) in its server logs to deliver the
        site and protect against abuse. That processing is governed by
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. External links</h2>
      <p>
        This site links to outside resources &mdash; research papers, videos, doctors' websites,
        and the r/noburp community. We aren't responsible for their content or privacy practices;
        please review their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Your rights &amp; contact</h2>
      <p>
        Because we don't collect personal data, there's nothing for us to access, correct, or
        delete. If you have a privacy question, email
        <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Regional privacy rights (GDPR, CCPA, and similar)</h2>
      <p>
        Laws such as the EU/UK GDPR and the California Consumer Privacy Act give people rights over
        their personal data. Because this site collects, sells, and shares no personal data, there is
        nothing for us to disclose, delete, or opt out of. If we ever add something that does process
        personal data &mdash; for example, analytics &mdash; we will update this policy first and
        describe your choices.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This site is a general-audience educational resource and is not directed at children. We do
        not knowingly collect personal information from anyone, including children.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above will change with it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
